<h2 id="riff-4-utilize-the-open-e-string">Riff 4: Utilize the open E-string</h2>

<p>This one is a bit more â€œdelicateâ€, as youâ€™re not longer strumming throughout the 8 counts. Instead, you strum once on the first â€œ1â€ count, and then strum again on the next â€œ1â€ count. Otherwise, you want the melody notes I tab out to ring out cleanly. Note, for the Dm7 chord youâ€™ll need to unbarre your index finger to play the open E string in the first measure (tricky).</p>

